 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Feb. 26: Fiat India has offered a voluntary retirement scheme to some of its employees to rightsize operation. The VRS will conclude in the middle of March. It is being offered to blue-collar workers. Some weeks ago, the company announced a marketing agreement with Tata Motors which will also take off in March. 

 New Delhi, Feb. 26: The civil aviation ministry has set up a nine-member tripartite committee to consider proposals for modernisation of airports and the issue of workers? job security. The panel will be headed by A.K. Misra, member planning, Airports Authority of India. 

 Kochi, Feb. 26: The government has earmarked Rs 1,00,000 crore till 2011-2012, Union Shipping minister T.R. Baalu said today. Of this, Rs 60,000 crore will be used for improving facilities in various ports and Rs 40,000 crore will be spent on the shipping sector, Baalu told reporters here. Most of the fund will come from the private sector.

